The paper deals with the problem of quantifying the cryptographic content of probability distributions, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a new monotone called the residual total correlation, which is a concept related to data structures (cs.DS) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the public discussion model, which is a topic related to computer communication (cs.CC).
